cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with load balancing in data center networks. Other likely sub-categories include Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as the proposed architecture is distributed and scalable, and Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it involves designing a control plane for load balancing. Additionally, the paper may also fall under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as load balancing is crucial for ensuring security and preventing DDoS attacks, and Performance (cs.PF) as the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed architecture.
